bNOPAx-s6.memHandModelNotes: Northern Parula were rarely encountered in forest tracts of <100 Ha (Robbins et al. 1989) and Bushman and Therres 1988 (in NatureServe 2005) state that forest fragmentation may negatively impact populations in tracts smaller than 65-100 hectares.  GA-GAP used a patch size requirement of 30ha, but could not find any supporting literature for this number.  Probability of detecting species in bottomland forests of widths > 500m was 100% (Kilgo et al. 1998).  Amy Silvano 6jun05
